   <exercise><p>The linked list implementation given above is called a <term>singly linked
               list</term> because each node has a single reference to the next node in the
           sequence. An alternative implementation is known as a <term>doubly linked
               list</term>. In this implementation, each node has a reference to the next
   node (commonly called <em>next</em>) as well as a reference to the preceding
   node (commonly called <em>back</em>). The head reference also contains two
   references, one to the first node in the linked list and one to the
   last. Code this implementation in Python.</p></exercise>

